p: The yield of essential oil was 0.41 % ( v/ w). Density of essential oil at 25 °C was 0.831 g/mL and refractive index was 1.391 at 25 °C. Based on the obtained results in GC/MS, twenty-five compounds were identified, indicating 93.01% of the total essential oil ( Table S1, Supplementary Materials). The major constituents were α-pinene (24.7%), 1,8-cineole (19.6%), and linalool (12.6%), respectively.
